Arsenal legend, Thierry Henry, has hailed RB Leipzig forward, Christopher Nkunku, who is reportedly attracting interest from Chelsea and Manchester United this summer. Henry said he loves watching Nkunku, adding that the world wants the 24-year-old. Nkunku has been in brilliant form for Leipzig this season. The French star has scored a remarkable 35 goals and contributed 20 assists in 51 appearances in all competitions for the Bundesliga club. “I do love watching him. Goals and assists. He is just having fun this season, but he is adding goals this year,” Henry told CBS Sports (via Team Talk). “He’s in the national team now. His confidence… the world wants him.”